author: johnh
msg: gadgets.rpc early-message queueing. Any message sent before the relevant transport is ready to send it is now queued, and sent upon completion of a readiness handshake.

This ensures that all messages sent through gadgets.rpc reach their destination, regardless of timing issues associated with transport setup eg. sending several messages before the RMR handshake is complete.
Updated rpctest_container.html test harness to support deferred gadget attachment, in order to test this functionality.
Also added "log.js" to core feature.xml in the container section, so that gadgets.log functionality is available to container-sourced rpc.js.
